rComments: I was so nervous going into this course but it was not bad at all. He is a bit disorganized, he gave us a lot of assigment and quizzes in the last 3 weeks but they help you prepare for the final. The exam questions were fair and clear. Some TAs made content more difficult but just go to fsg and youll be fine. The course made me love math again.
Learned a lot in this class. Thankfully there were many opportunities given to learn from mistakes and correct them.

There is no instruction of formatting (reporting) your answers on exams. You will lose marks for not exhausting your problem to the nth degree. ie. effect size, r value t value power etc etc. Also tests/exams are marked by many different ta's and if they make a mistake (which happens) it is never corrected and you do not receive the mark deserved

I really enjoyed taking statistics with prof pare. I really am not a math person but he made the content interesting and knew his stuff. There was a lot of work after the midterm but he warned us about that early on so I was prepared.

At first, you would think what an easy course. After midterms, you would be like what the hell. He is a nice teacher that thinks he is informing the class about the material, but he isn't. GO to fsgs & tutorials, thank me later. After midterms, that when he will give you all the assignments and quizzes. P.S. there are no quizzes in tutorial
Great course!

Crammed 6 assignments and 5 tests in the last month of class. Did not activate Blackboard or Quercus until 3 weeks after class started. Never used the textbook. Doesnt keep class engaged during lecture

Honestly the nicest prof I've had! He makes statistics really clear to understand and is always willing to provide extra help when needed. I highly recommend taking stats with him because it's a fairly easy A! His exams are super similar to the practice questions he posts as well :)

dwayne was an excellent teacher! like others have written here, he knows what he is talking about and cares about his students. if you are looking here to decide if you should take a course with him, the answer is yes.

One of the worst professors I've ever had at UofT... Barely teaches and doesn't understand his own content. He doesn't keep up with the syllabus, therefore students suffer on midterms. Forget about asking for help! He will go on week long breaks from him email (on critical periods such as before exams/assignments) & never will answer you anyways!

One of the best prof's I've had the pleasure of learning from. Like many have already stated, this guy really cares about his students. Lectures are clear, concise with real-world examples. As someone who was terrified to take this class, I have been pleasantly surprised. If you need to take this course, take it with Dwayne. He's great.
Was initially worried about this course since I'm not good with math. But Dwayne taught the course so well that it was inspiring and enjoyable. Would definitely take another course with this prof

Dwayne definitely cares about his students. He genuinely wants everyone to do well. He makes lectures interesting. This course is easy to do well in, as long as you pay attention in lectures and attend FSG's and tutorials. Dwayne has a good course break down, where you have many chances to earn marks! Also, the exams are extremely fair.
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'Amazing lectures', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Dwayne is one the best prof at UTSC. He actually makes Stats FUN!  It's really not that hard to get a good grade in his class as long as you show up for lecture, tutorial and take good notes.  Will definitely take another course with him!

Dwayne was a really nice prof who cared for his students. He was very considerate and provided multiple opportunities for students to get bonus marks to redeem a bad quiz/ assignment. Attending tutorials and FSGs are HIGHLY recommended and will help you by a mile! exams and midterms were nothing unexpected. PRACTICE questions and you'll be A-ok! :)
Amazing prof & class! Both A01 and A02 have convinced me to continue taking psychology courses.

This was my easiest class yet. I was enrolled online, never watched a lecture and still passed with a high mark. From what I heard, his lectures were based from the textbook which is MANDATORY for this course. Take notes from the textbook and you can get an A.

Dwayne is such an understanding person and spends his time making sure that his students understand the course content. If you don't understand something, make sure to ask him questions, and he'll definitely clarify for you. Although he leaves grading and assignments for the last moment, he's a humorous and knowledgable prof!

I really enjoyed the intro psychology course taught by professor pare. He was a really great teacher and he was very approachable. I look forward to having him again as a professor.   btw, I have no idea how some people comment on exam content when this is his first time offering this course (and we haven't even had the exam yet!) odd.
exam is heavily textbook based, some questions are from the lectures. PREPARE TO MEMORIZE THE ENTIRE TEXTBOOK

Dwayne was one of the best prof's I have had here at UTSC. I was not looking forward to this class at all, and honestly, he made it worth it. His lecture slides were clear, and straight to the point. He covered everything essential to the course and made data analysis very enjoyable. I would love to take another course with him as the prof.

AMAZING!! Prof. Pare is very knowledgable and his course is well planned out. Taking memory and cognition with Prof. Pare has been a great experience because his teaching style keeps it interesting. Anyone that is confused or can't find their grades means they aren't paying attention in class or are not reading the announcements. - simple as that.

VERY DISORGANIZED! It's unreal how disorganized this guy can be! Every week in lecture he will tell you that the grades will come out the same day but it's all LIESSS... Doesn't even follow the marking scheme in the syllabus. He falls behind in giving quizzes and then he has to come up with something else to fix it.... DISORGANIZED!!!

Best professor at UTSC. You can tell he is very passionate and cares about his student. I don't like Math but taking PSYC08 with him was fun and surprisingly I got a good grade because I understood everything!

Professor Pare is one of THE best professors at UTSC. Trust me. It can be very rare to find a prof that TRULY CARES about their students. He is so approachable and friendly, and ALWAYS available to help. His courses are not easy, but they are FAIR. He actually listens to student feedback. His lectures are interesting. I wish he taught more courses.

This was a brand new course created by Prof. Pare, and it was amazing! He allowed us to help guide the course structure which made for an engaging experience. The MATLAB skills taught will be very useful when working in a real lab. One of my favorite courses at UTSC!

He is a great professor and a nice human being but he is extremely disorganized and always leaves everything till the last minute when the students are preparing for mid-term. The class is really easy though but remember to study his slides as well as the book.

Dwayne is a good Prof! He's sometimes disorganized but his lectures are really interesting and fun. Though he tests the textbook (make sure to read and take good notes), his lectures help supplement the material and gives you good examples to grasp the concepts. His assignments are decent too!
Hands down the best prof at utsc. He actually CARES about his students

SUPER HELPFUL! No like seriously one of the most nicest professors out there. UofT hasn't broken him down and taken the spunk of teaching away from him, and I hope they never do. Attend his classes, he enjoys teaching and loves his students. And the one of the nicest profs as well

He knows his stuff and when you have questions he explains them very clearly. He doesn't respond to emails and is very disorganized but he genuinely wants you to do well and is a good and engaging prof overall. His exam is very fair and you should be able to get perfect on quiz/ZAPs. I will always remember the holiday assignment it was fun!
A great prof and a great person. He cares about the students + the work. In all honesty, you won't find a better prof at utsc than Prof Pare.

Very easy class, good distribution of marks (quizzes + midterms + final). Very friendly and chill guy! If you read the textbook, you can get 80+ but he does a good job in explaining the information too.
Absolute best professor I have ever had since start of University!! I would definitely take his 3rd year courses if he had any. I am male.

Extremely easy if you do all the little assignments he assigns. His entire lecture material is based on the textbook, but the textbook explains the concepts in much more detail and clairity, renderings his lectures useless. However, he is a great guy who's very passionate about his line of work and research.
DJ Richie-Rich is very helpful, knowledgeable, and friendly. He is an excellent prof.
Great Prof!
I am only halfway through the course and am loving it! Professor Pare's lectures are interesting, and he is very responsive to student emails. The weekly activities are also very helpful!

Dwayne assigns a lot of "little work", like online quizzes, which get tedious, and he can be disorganized.  But he gives you so many opportunities to improve your mark, he truly wants you to learn.  He is deep, knowledgeable, and incredibly friendly.  Occasionally unclear, but incredibly helpful, and will make up for his own disorganization.
Amazing Prof - one of the best I have had at the University of Toronto.

Very helpful! Very enthusiastic about the course material! And truly cares about student learning on top of that! Some reviews mention him 'not answering emails' or being 'disorganized' - however this is farther from the truth for the current courses he teaches. Great Prof!!!

This prof is is very good at explaining concepts. It is evident that he is knowlwdge about course material and is passionate about psych. He is extremely helpful and allows us to have question/ answer sessions. By far one of the best profs at utsc. Anyone who cant understand material through his teaching shouldnt take data analysis

This professor is a nice guy in general but is completely unprofessional and disorganized. He gave us a syllabus 2 weeks after school already started, keeps changing due dates to the point where they are ambiguous, doesnt follow the syllabus right, and uses stupid online resources in which he makes it confusing to know which ones you need to do!
